ean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret was born in 1473, in Bath, Somerset, England. She had at least 2 sons with Richard Packard II. She died in 1531, in Suffolk, England, at the age of 58."},"et":{"1473–1531":"1473–1531","1468–1531":"1468–1531","1492–1553":"1492–1553","1500–Male":"1500–Surnud","abt 1500":"umbes 1500","1468":"1468","1500":"1500","1531":"1531","1553":"1553","1 November 1492":"1. november 1492","1473":"1473","1492":"1492","Bath, Somerset, England":"Bath, Somerset, England","of Saperton, Gloucester, Eng.":"Sapperton, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Stonham Aspall, Mid Suffolk, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Stonham Aspal, Suffolk, England","Earl, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England"},"fi":{"1473–1531":"1473–1531","1468–1531":"1468–1531","1492–1553":"1492–1553","1500–Male":"1500–Kuollut","abt 1500":"noin 1500","1468":"1468","1500":"1500","1531":"1531","1553":"1553","1 November 1492":"1. marraskuuta 1492","1473":"1473","1492":"1492","Bath, Somerset, England":"Bath, Somerset, England","of Saperton, Gloucester, Eng.":"Sapperton, Gloucestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Stonham Aspall, Mid Suffolk, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Stonham Aspal, Suffolk, England","Earl, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England"},"fr":{"1473–1531":"1473–1531","1468–1531":"1468–1531","1492–1553":"1492–1553","1500–Male":"1500–Décédé","abt 1500":"environ 1500","1468":"1468","1500":"1500","1531":"1531","1553":"1553","1 November 1492":"1 novembre 1492","1473":"1473","1492":"1492","Bath, Somerset, England":"Bath, Somerset, Angleterre","of Saperton, Gloucester, Eng.":"Sapperton, Gloucestershire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Stonham Aspall, Mid Suffolk, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Stonham Aspal, Suffolk, Angleterre","Earl, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Margaret est née en 1473, à Bath, Somerset, Angleterre. Elle a eu au moins 2 fils avec Richard Packar